(43, 8, 19, 40, 11, 25, 25, 'ye should have known my Father also', 'Knowledge of the Father', 'This connection highlights the theme of knowing God. In John 8:19, Jesus emphasizes that knowing Him is essential to knowing the Father, while in Matthew 11:25, He thanks the Father for revealing truths to the humble, suggesting a deeper understanding of God is accessible to those who are open.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 19, 46, 15, 34, 34, 'ye neither know me, nor my Father', 'Knowledge of God', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of knowing God. In John 8:19, Jesus states that knowing Him equates to knowing the Father, while 1 Corinthians 15:34 highlights that some lack the knowledge of God, which is presented as a shameful condition.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 19, 24, 24, 7, 7, 'ye should have known my Father also', 'Knowledge of God', 'This connection highlights the theme of knowing God. In John 8:19, Jesus emphasizes that knowing Him is essential to knowing the Father, while Jeremiah 24:7 speaks of God giving a heart to know Him.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 19, 42, 10, 21, 22, 'Ye neither know me, nor my Father', 'Knowledge of the Father and Son', 'This connection highlights the theme of knowing the Father and the Son. Both passages emphasize that true knowledge of God comes through revelation and relationship, as seen in Jesus'' statements about knowing Him and the Father.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 20, 43, 7, 30, 30, 'for his hour was not yet come', 'Connection of Timing in Jesus'' Ministry', 'Both passages emphasize that no one laid hands on Jesus because ''his hour was not yet come.'' This repetition highlights the significance of divine timing in the events surrounding Jesus'' ministry.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 20, 41, 12, 41, 41, 'the treasury', 'Connection through the Treasury', 'Both passages emphasize the treasury as a significant location in the temple where Jesus teaches and observes. The mention of the treasury in both contexts highlights its importance in Jesus'' ministry.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 20, 43, 7, 8, 8, NULL, 'Connection of Timing in Jesus'' Ministry', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of timing in Jesus'' ministry. In John 7:8, Jesus states that his time has not yet come, and in John 8:20, it is noted that his hour was not yet come, highlighting the significance of divine timing in his actions.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 20, 40, 27, 6, 6, 'treasury', 'Connection of Treasury References', 'This connection highlights the theme of the treasury in both passages. In John 8:20, Jesus teaches in the treasury, while in Matthew 27:6, the chief priests discuss the lawfulness of placing blood money into the treasury.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 20, 13, 9, 26, 26, 'the treasury', 'Connection of Treasury Themes', 'This connection highlights the significance of the treasury in both passages. In John 8:20, Jesus teaches in the treasury, while 1 Chronicles 9:26 mentions Levites overseeing the treasuries of the house of God.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 20, 42, 13, 31, 33, 'for his hour was not yet come', 'Jesus'' Mission and Timing', 'This connection highlights the theme of Jesus'' determined mission despite threats. In both passages, Jesus indicates that his time has not yet come, emphasizing his control over the timeline of his ministry.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 20, 42, 20, 19, 19, 'no man laid hands on him', 'Conflict with Authorities', 'Both passages emphasize the tension between Jesus and the religious leaders. In John, no one lays hands on him because ''his hour was not yet come,'' while in Luke, the chief priests and scribes seek to lay hands on him, indicating their desire to act against him.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 21, 43, 7, 34, 34, 'ye shall seek me', 'Seeking and Inability to Follow', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of seeking Jesus and the inability to follow Him. The repetition of the phrase ''ye shall seek me'' underscores a shared message about the consequences of not being able to come where He is.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 21, 43, 8, 24, 24, NULL, 'Connection of Sin and Belief', 'Both passages emphasize the consequence of dying in sins, linking it to the necessity of belief in Jesus. The repetition of the phrase ''ye shall die in your sins'' underscores the seriousness of rejecting his identity.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 21, 46, 15, 17, 18, NULL, 'Connection of Sin and Faith', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of being ''in your sins.'' John 8:21 warns of dying in sins without Jesus, while 1 Corinthians 15:17 states that faith is vain if Christ is not raised, leaving believers still in their sins.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 21, 11, 18, 10, 10, 'ye shall seek me', 'Seeking and Absence', 'This connection highlights the theme of seeking and the absence of the one sought. In both passages, there is an emphasis on searching for someone who is not present, leading to dire consequences.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 21, 12, 2, 16, 17, 'ye shall seek me', 'Seeking and Not Finding', 'This connection highlights the theme of seeking without success. In John 8:21, Jesus indicates that those who seek Him will not find Him, paralleling the failure of the fifty men in 2 Kings 2:16-17 to find Elijah despite their efforts.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 21, 18, 20, 11, 11, 'die in your sins', 'Connection of Sin and Death', 'This connection highlights the theme of sin leading to death. In John 8:21, Jesus speaks of dying in sins, while Job 20:11 mentions the consequences of youthful sin resulting in death.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 21, 19, 73, 18, 20, 'ye shall seek me', 'Destruction and Seeking God', 'This connection highlights the theme of seeking God amidst impending destruction. In John 8:21, Jesus warns of dying in sins, while Psalms 73:18-20 describes those set in slippery places leading to destruction.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 22, 43, 8, 52, 52, 'ye cannot come', 'Death and Eternal Life', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of death. In John 8:22, the Jews question Jesus about where he is going, implying a fear of death, while in John 8:52, they challenge his claim about never tasting death, highlighting their misunderstanding of his message.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 22, 19, 22, 6, 6, NULL, 'Despair and Rejection Theme', 'This connection highlights the theme of despair and rejection present in both passages. In John 8:22, the Jews question Jesus'' fate, reflecting a sense of confusion and rejection, while Psalms 22:6 expresses deep humiliation and being despised.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 22, 19, 31, 18, 18, 'ye cannot come', 'Silencing of Contemptuous Speech', 'This connection highlights the theme of silencing those who speak against the righteous. In John 8:22, the Jews question Jesus'' fate, reflecting their contempt, while Psalms 31:18 calls for the silencing of lying lips that speak against the righteous.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 22, 43, 7, 20, 20, NULL, 'Connection of Accusations of Violence', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of accusations against Jesus regarding violence. In John 7:20, the people suggest he has a devil for supposedly planning to kill, while in John 8:22, the Jews question if he will kill himself, indicating a shared concern about his intentions.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 22, 58, 12, 3, 3, NULL, 'Contradiction and Endurance', 'This connection highlights the theme of enduring contradiction. In John 8:22, the Jews question Jesus'' fate, reflecting their misunderstanding and opposition, while Hebrews 12:3 encourages believers to consider Jesus'' endurance against such contradiction.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 22, 58, 13, 13, 13, 'Whither I go, ye cannot come', 'Rejection and Following Christ', 'This connection highlights the theme of leaving behind societal norms to follow Jesus. In John 8:22, the Jews question where Jesus is going, indicating a separation, while Hebrews 13:13 encourages believers to go forth to Him, embracing His reproach.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 23, 43, 3, 31, 31, 'I am from above', 'Connection of Origin and Authority', 'Both passages emphasize the distinction between those from above and those from the earth. They highlight the authority of the one who comes from above, contrasting it with earthly origins.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 23, 43, 17, 14, 14, 'I am not of this world', 'Connection of Worldly Origin', 'Both passages emphasize the distinction between those who are ''of this world'' and those who are ''not of this world.'' This connection highlights the spiritual identity of Jesus and His followers in contrast to worldly values.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 23, 62, 2, 15, 16, 'ye are of this world', 'Worldly vs. Heavenly Perspectives', 'This connection highlights the contrast between being ''of this world'' and the call to not love ''the world.'' Both passages emphasize a distinction between earthly desires and a higher, divine origin.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 23, 62, 4, 5, 6, 'ye are of this world', 'Worldly vs. Divine Origins', 'This connection highlights the distinction between those who are ''of this world'' and those who are ''from above.'' Both passages emphasize the differing responses to truth based on one''s origin, with the world hearing its own and not recognizing the divine.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 23, 59, 4, 4, 4, 'ye are of this world', 'Worldly vs. Divine Perspectives', 'This connection highlights the contrast between being ''of this world'' and the enmity with God that comes from friendship with the world. Both passages emphasize the distinction between divine origins and worldly affiliations.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 8, 23, 19, 17, 4, 4, 'I am not of this world', 'Connection of Worldly vs. Divine', 'This connection highlights the distinction between worldly influences and divine guidance. In John 8:23, the contrast of ''this world'' and ''above'' parallels the idea in Psalms 17:4 of being kept from destructive paths through divine words.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
